{"TopicDetails": {"type": 0, "ccm2Id": 43992317, "cftId": 0, "identifier": "RFCS-01-2021-RPJ", "title": "RFCS-2021 Coal Research Projects", "publicationDateLong": 1624924800000, "callIdentifier": "RFCS-2021", "callTitle": "RFCS-2021", "callccm2Id": 43992347, "allowPartnerSearch": true, "workProgrammepart": {"id": 5872, "ccm_id": 44172546, "wp_part": "RFCS-2021", "wp_year": "RFCS-2021", "wp_title": "RFCS-2021", "wp_website": "https://ec.europa.eu/info/research-and-innovation/funding/funding-opportunities/funding-programmes-and-open-calls/research-fund-coal-and-steel-rfcs_en", "wp_document": "https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/rfcs/wp-call/2021/rfcs-2021_en.pdf"}, "frameworkProgramme": {"id": 43252449, "abbreviation": "RFCS2027", "description": "Research Fund for Coal & Steel (RFCS)"}, "programmeDivision": [{"id": 43252470, "abbreviation": "RFCS-1-1", "description": "RFCS-1-1"}], "topicMGAs": [], "tags": ["Coal", "RFCS"], "keywords": ["Research Objective Art.5", "Research Objective Art.7", "Research Objective Art.6", "Research Objective Art.4"], "sme": false, "actions": [{"status": {"id": 31094503, "abbreviation": "Closed", "description": "Closed"}, "types": [{"typeOfAction": "RFCS-PJG RFCS Project Grants", "typeOfMGA": [{"id": 43250365, "abbreviation": "RFCS-AG", "description": "RFCS Action Grant Budget-Based"}]}], "plannedOpeningDate": "29 June 2021", "submissionProcedure": {"id": 31094504, "abbreviation": "single-stage", "description": "single-stage"}, "deadlineDates": ["22 September 2021"]}], "latestInfos": [{"approvalDate": "Jun 29, 2021 1:39:19 PM", "lastChangeDate": "Jun 28, 2021 7:14:50 PM", "content": "<p><span class=\"topicdescriptionkind\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Specific Challenge</span><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">On the 1st of December 2019, a new European Commission entered into service for the present quinquennium 2019-2024. The new College of Commissioners, under the presidency of Ms Ursula von der Leyen, reset the Commission&rsquo;s commitment to &ldquo;tackling climate and environmental-related challenges that is this generation&rsquo;s defining task&rdquo;. The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?qid=1588580774040&amp;uri=CELEX:52019DC0640\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(0, 68, 148); cursor: pointer;\">European Green Deal Communication</a>, presented by the Commission in December 2019, is a new growth strategy that aims to transform the EU into a fair and prosperous society, with a modern, resource-efficient and competitive economy where there are no net emissions of greenhouse gases in 2050 and where economic growth is decoupled from resource use.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Within the most pertinent lines for the RFCS research programme arising from the European Green Deal Communication, applicants to RFCS-2021 call for the coal topic should consider the following elements when preparing their proposals:</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">- A power sector must be developed that is based largely on renewable sources, complemented by the&nbsp;<span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: bolder; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: eui-bold, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">rapid phasing out of coal</span><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- The EU should also reinforce current initiatives [..] on cross-cutting climate and environment issues. This may include ending global fossil fuel subsidies in line with G20 commitments, [..] phasing out all new coal plant construction, and action to reduce methane emissions<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- Focus on the regions and sectors that are most affected by the transition because they depend on fossil fuels or carbon-intensive processes<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- Protect the citizens and workers most vulnerable to the transition, providing access to re-skilling programmes, jobs in new economic sectors</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"topicdescriptionkind\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Scope</span><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Proposals submitted to the RFCS programme on the coal research topic must address at least one of the respective RFCS Research Objectives of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?qid=1591955899856&amp;uri=CELEX:32008D0376\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(0, 68, 148); cursor: pointer;\">Council Decision 2008/376/EC</a>&nbsp;(Articles 4 to 7) and should relate to the European Green Deal Communication&rsquo;s elements listed in the Introduction chapter of the RFCS 2021 Information Package Part 1.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">When filling in the proposal, applicants are asked to indicate which research objectives are addressed and which of the European Green Deal Communication&rsquo;s elements the proposal relates to.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Each proposal shall include an assessment of anticipated industrial, economic, social and environmental benefits, as stated in the Article 26 of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?qid=1591955899856&amp;uri=CELEX:32008D0376\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(0, 68, 148); cursor: pointer;\">Council Decision 2008/376/EC</a>&nbsp;&ldquo;Content of proposals&rdquo;.</p>"}], "budgetOverviewJSONItem": {"budgetTopicActionMap": {"3341034": [{"action": "RFCS-02-2021-AM - RFCS-PJG RFCS Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "29 June 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["22 September 2021"], "budgetYearMap": {"2021": 11362500}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}, {"action": "RFCS-01-2021-PDP - RFCS-PJG RFCS Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "29 June 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["22 September 2021"], "budgetYearMap": {"2021": 11362500}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}, {"action": "RFCS-01-2021-AM - RFCS-PJG RFCS Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "29 June 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["22 September 2021"], "budgetYearMap": {"2021": 11362500}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}, {"action": "RFCS-02-2021-RPJ - RFCS-PJG RFCS Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "29 June 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["22 September 2021"], "budgetYearMap": {"2021": 11362500}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}, {"action": "RFCS-02-2021-PDP - RFCS-PJG RFCS Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "29 June 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["22 September 2021"], "budgetYearMap": {"2021": 11362500}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}, {"action": "RFCS-01-2021-RPJ - RFCS-PJG RFCS Project Grants", "plannedOpeningDate": "29 June 2021", "deadlineModel": "single-stage", "deadlineDates": ["22 September 2021"], "budgetYearMap": {"2021": 11362500}, "budgetTopicActionMap": {}}]}, "budgetYearsColumns": ["2021"]}, "conditions": "<p><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\">Conditions<br />\r\n<br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></b></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Admissibility conditions&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">are</span><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">described in Part 2-Calls for proposals and Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;of the Information Package 2021.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Proposal page limits and layout</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;are described </span>in Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;and Part 4-Guide and Manual of the Information Package 2021. The templates of Forms Part B are available for download in the Submission System and the page limits for each document are as well specified inside these templates.</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Eligible countries </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">are&nbsp;described in Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;</span>of the Information Package 2021 and in the RFCS legal basis.</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Other eligibility conditions</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;are described in Part 2-Calls for proposals&nbsp;and Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;of&nbsp;</span>the Information Package 2021.</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b>Financial and operational capacity and exclusion </b>are&nbsp;described <span lang=\"EN-US\">in Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;</span>of the Information Package 2021.</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"FR-BE\">Evaluation and award&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=\"FR-BE\">are described</span><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;in Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;</span>and in more details in Part 4-Guide and Manual&nbsp;of the Information Package 2021 (Part 4 is a Guide for Applicants and Manual for Evaluation and Selection of the proposals).</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Award criteria, scoring and thresholds</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;</span>are described<span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;in Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;</span>and in more details in Part 4-Guide and Manual&nbsp;of the Information Package 2021 (Part 4 is a Guide for Applicants and Manual for Evaluation and Selection of the proposals).</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\">Submission and evaluation processes</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;<span style=\"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\">are described<span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;in Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">and in more details in Part 4-Guide and Manual</span><span style=\"color: rgb(0, 0, 0);\">&nbsp;of the Information Package 2021 (Part 4 is a Guide for Applicants and Manual for Evaluation and Selection of the proposals)</span>&nbsp;and the</span>&nbsp;</span><a href=\"https://webgate.ec.europa.eu/funding-tenders-opportunities/display/OM/Online+Manual\" target=\"_blank\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">Online Manual</span></a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Indicative timeline for evaluation and grant agreement </span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">are&nbsp;</span>described in Part 2-Calls for proposals&nbsp;of&nbsp;the Information Package 2021.</li>\r\n</ul>\n<ul>\r\n    <li><b><span lang=\"EN-US\">Legal and financial set-up of the grants&nbsp;</span></b><span lang=\"EN-US\">are&nbsp;</span>described<span lang=\"EN-US\">&nbsp;in Part 3-General Provisions&nbsp;</span>of the Information Package 2021.</li>\r\n</ul>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><b><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"font-size: 12pt; line-height: 18.4px; color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\">Documents</span></b><b style=\"color: rgb(64, 64, 64);\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">:</span></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;&#10;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/rfcs/wp-call/2021/call-fiche_rfcs-2021_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Information Package : Parts 1 - 4</a><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:&#10;EN-US\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/rfcs/temp-form/af/af_rfcs_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Sample application form ([ToA])</a> </span><span style=\"color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191\">&mdash;</span><i style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:&#10;normal\"><span style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;&#10;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\"> <span lang=\"EN-US\">call-specific application forms are available in the Submission System</span></span></i><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:&#10;EN-US\"> <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;&#10;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">Content of Evaluation Forms&nbsp;</span><span style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191\">&mdash;</span><i style=\"mso-bidi-font-style:normal\"><span lang=\"EN-US\" style=\"color:#404040;&#10;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-ansi-language:EN-US\">&nbsp;</span></i><em>in the Part 4-Guide and Manual&nbsp;of the Information Package 2021 Annex II</em></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:4.0pt;line-height:normal;tab-stops:&#10;191.4pt\"><span style=\"color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:&#10;191;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB;mso-no-proof:yes\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/docs/2021-2027/rfcs/agr-contr/mga_rfcs_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">RFCS General MGA v1.0</a></span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/ALL/?uri=CELEX:32018R1046&amp;qid=1535046024012\"><span lang=\"EN-US\">EU Financial Regulation 2018/1046</span></a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/HTML/?uri=CELEX:32008D0376&amp;qid=1583750615239&amp;from=EN\" target=\"_blank\">RFCS legal basis in force at the opening of the call in June 2021</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/publications/rfcs-funded-projects_en\" target=\"_blank\">RFCS funded projects history</a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>", "supportInfo": "<p><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/research-and-innovation/funding/funding-opportunities/funding-programmes-and-open-calls/research-fund-coal-and-steel-rfcs_en\" target=\"_blank\">RFCS Website</a>&nbsp;- for general information on RFCS Programme</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\">For help related to this</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\">&nbsp;</span><b style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\">call</b><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\">, please contact:</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt;\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 9pt; color: red;\"><a href=\"mailto:rea-rfcs@ec.europa.eu?subject=Request%20via%20the%20F%26T%20Topic%20page&amp;body=Dear%20RFCS%20Team%2C%0AI%20am%20on%20the%20F%26T%20Topic%20%5Btopic%20name%5D%20page.%20%0ACould%20you%20please%20help%20with%20the%20following%20%3A%20%5Btext%5D%0AThank%20you.%0ABest%20regards%2C%0A\" target=\"_blank\">rea-rfcs@ec.europa.eu</a></span></p>\r\n<p>For questions related to RFCS policy aspects, please contact: <a href=\"mailto:rtd-steel-coal@ec.europa.eu?subject=RFCS%20policy%20question&amp;body=Dear%20RFCS%20Team%20in%20charge%20of%20policy%20aspects%2C%0AI%20am%20on%20the%20F%26T%20Topic%20%5Btopic%20name%5D%20page.%20%0ACould%20you%20please%20help%20with%20the%20following%20%3A%20%5Btext%5D%0AThank%20you.%0ABest%20regards%2C%0A\" target=\"_blank\">rtd-steel-coal@ec.europa.eu</a></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal;\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/portal/screen/support/faq;grantAndTendertype=1;categories=p_submission_eval;programme=null;actions=;keyword=;period=null\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Funding &amp; Tenders Portal FAQ</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&ndash; Submission of proposals.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal;\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/funding-tenders/opportunities/portal/screen/support/helpdesks/contact-form\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">IT Helpdesk</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&ndash; Contact the IT helpdesk for questions such as forgotten passwords, access rights and roles, technical aspects of submission of proposals, etc.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal;\"><a href=\"https://webgate.ec.europa.eu/funding-tenders-opportunities/display/OM/Online+Manual\"><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">Online Manual</span></a><span style=\"font-size: 9pt; font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\">&nbsp;&ndash; Step-by-step online guide through the Portal processes from proposal preparation and submission to reporting on your on-going project. Valid for all 2021-2027 programmes.</span></p>", "sepTemplate": "<p>To access the Electronic Submission Service, please click on the submission-button next to the <strong>type of action</strong> and the <strong>type of model grant agreement</strong> that corresponds to your proposal. You will then be asked to confirm your choice, as it cannot be changed in the submission system. Upon confirmation, you will be linked to the correct entry point.</p>\r\n<p>To access existing draft proposals for this topic, please login to the Funding &amp; Tenders Portal and select the My Proposals page of the My Area section.</p>", "links": [], "additionalDossiers": [], "infoPackDossiers": [], "callDetailsJSONItem": {"additionalInfo": "<p><span style=\"color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px;\">The Research Programme of the Research Fund for Coal and Steel (RFCS) is a funding programme of the European Union intended to support research and innovation in the sectors related to the coal and steel industry.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">On the 1st of December 2019, a new European Commission entered into service for the present quinquennium 2019-2024. The new College of Commissioners, under the presidency of Ms Ursula von der Leyen, reset the Commission&rsquo;s commitment to &ldquo;tackling climate and environmental-related challenges that is this generation&rsquo;s defining task&rdquo;.&nbsp; The&nbsp;<a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?qid=1588580774040&amp;uri=CELEX:52019DC0640\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(0, 68, 148); cursor: pointer;\">European Green Deal Communication</a>, presented by the Commission in December 2019, is a new growth strategy that aims to transform the EU into a fair and prosperous society, with a modern, resource-efficient and competitive economy where there are no net emissions of greenhouse gases in 2050 and where economic growth is decoupled from resource use.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Within the most pertinent lines for the RFCS research programme arising from the European Green Deal Communication, applicants to RFCS-2021 call should consider the following elements when preparing their proposals:</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">- Energy-intensive industries, such as steel [..] are indispensable to Europe&rsquo;s economy, as they supply several key value chains. The decarbonisation and modernisation of this sector is essential.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- The Commission will support clean steel breakthrough technologies leading to a zero-carbon steel making process by 2030.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- A power sector must be developed that is based largely on renewable sources, complemented by the rapid phasing out of coal<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- The EU should also reinforce current initiatives [..] on cross-cutting climate and environment issues. This may include ending global fossil fuel subsidies in line with G20 commitments, [..] phasing out all new coal plant construction, and action to reduce methane emissions<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- Focus on the regions and sectors that are most affected by the transition because they depend on fossil fuels or carbon-intensive processes<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box;\" />\r\n- Protect the citizens and workers most vulnerable to the transition, providing access to re-skilling programmes, jobs in new economic sectors</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 1rem 0px; padding: 0px; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Further relevant communications on future directions given by the European Commission, such as a New Industrial Strategy for Europe, Just Transition Mechanism and the Sustainable European Investment Plan, can be found at:</p>\r\n<ul style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: eui-default, Arial, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 15px; list-style: none; display: inline-block; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">\r\n    <li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px 7px; list-style: disc;\"><a href=\"https://ec.europa.eu/info/sites/info/files/communication-eu-industrial-strategy-march-2020_en.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(0, 68, 148); cursor: pointer;\">A New Industrial Strategy for Europe&nbsp;</a></li>\r\n    <li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px 7px; list-style: disc;\"><a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?qid=1579099555315&amp;uri=COM:2020:22:FIN\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(0, 68, 148); cursor: pointer;\">Just Transition Mechanism - proposal for Regulation COM/2020/22</a>&nbsp;</li>\r\n    <li style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 1.618; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px 7px; list-style: disc;\"><a href=\"https://eur-lex.europa.eu/legal-content/EN/TXT/?qid=1588582651667&amp;uri=CELEX%3A52020DC0021\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; text-decoration-line: none; background-color: transparent; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; touch-action: manipulation; color: rgb(0, 68, 148); cursor: pointer;\">The Sustainable Europe Investment Plan</a><span style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-style: inherit; font-variant: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: inherit; margin: 0px; padding: 0px;\">&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>", "latestInfos": [{"approvalDate": "Feb 2, 2022 12:55:20 PM", "lastChangeDate": "Feb 2, 2022 12:55:20 PM", "content": "<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:&#10;Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#FFA53C;text-transform:uppercase;&#10;mso-fareast-language:EN-US\">EVALUATION results</span></b><b><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-font-family:&#10;Arial;text-transform:uppercase;mso-fareast-language:EN-US\"> <o:p></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">Published: 29.06.2021<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">Deadline: 22.09.2021<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">Available budget: EUR 11.362.500,00<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-01-2021 Coal</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IE\">: EUR 3 090 600,00&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 7pt;\">(RFCS-01-2021-AM, RFCS-01-2021-PDP, RFCS-01-2021-RPJ)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><strong><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-02-2021 Steel</span></strong><span lang=\"EN-IE\">: EUR 8.271.900,00&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 7pt;\">(RFCS-02-2021-AM, RFCS-02-2021-PDP, RFCS-02-2021-RPJ)</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">The results of the evaluation are as follows: <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">Number of proposals submitted: 111<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-01-2021 Coal: 28<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-02-2021 Steel: 83<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">Number of inadmissible proposals: 3<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-01-2021 Coal: 2<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-02-2021 Steel: 1<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">Number of ineligible proposals: 0<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">Number of above-threshold proposals: 87<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-01-2021 Coal: 19<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-02-2021 Steel: 68<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\">Total budget requested for above-threshold proposals: EUR 111.701.745,02<o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-01-2021 Coal: EUR 26.594.545,57<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom:0cm;margin-bottom:.0001pt\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\">RFCS-02-2021 Steel: EUR </span>85.107.199,45<span lang=\"EN-IE\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span lang=\"EN-IE\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">We recently informed the applicants about the evaluation results for their proposals. <o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">For questions, please contact <a href=\"mailto:REA-RFCS@ec.europa.eu\"><span style=\"font-size:10.5pt;mso-bidi-font-size:&#10;10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Verdana&quot;,sans-serif;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">REA-RFCS@ec.europa.eu</span></a><b><i><o:p></o:p></i></b></p>"}, {"approvalDate": "Jun 29, 2021 1:39:19 PM", "lastChangeDate": "Jun 29, 2021 1:39:19 PM", "content": "The submission session is now available for: RFCS-02-2021-AM(RFCS-PJG), RFCS-01-2021-PDP(RFCS-PJG), RFCS-01-2021-AM(RFCS-PJG), RFCS-02-2021-RPJ(RFCS-PJG), RFCS-02-2021-PDP(RFCS-PJG), RFCS-01-2021-RPJ(RFCS-PJG)"}], "hasForthcomingTopics": false, "hasOpenTopics": false, "allClosedTopics": true}}}